NAME: APPLICATION
DESCRIPTION: Flag for type of application being modeled

NAME: PROCESS
DESCRIPTION: Flag for type of process being modeled

NAME: SUBPROCESS
DESCRIPTION: Flag for type of subprocess being modeled

NAME: ITB
DESCRIPTION: Indicator for free surfaces or sharp interfaces

NAME: IFIN
DESCRIPTION: Selects the basis for termination of the calculation

NAME: FRCFIN
DESCRIPTION: Fill fraction (:envvar:`IFIN` = 2) or solid fraction (:envvar:`IFIN` = 3) for termination of the calculation

NAME: ITWFIN
DESCRIPTION: Number of times steps (cycles) to end calculation.

NAME: DLTSTDY
DESCRIPTION: Variation threshold below which the flow is considered steady state (in percent)

NAME: DTIMPX
DESCRIPTION: Maximum Courant number used to limit the time step size in the implicit advection model, :envvar:`IMPADV` = 1. Used in addition to any other limiting factors.

NAME: EPSHTC
DESCRIPTION: Multiplier for temperature iteration convergence criterion

NAME: OMEGHT
DESCRIPTION: Relaxation factor for implicit heat transfer and conduction

NAME: IMPHTC
DESCRIPTION: Heat transfer and conduction explicit/implicit flag

NAME: FCLEAN
DESCRIPTION: Fluid fraction cleanup coefficient for fluid #1. Throws away fluid #1 "mist" regions where local (isolated) fluid fraction within a cell is less than :envvar:`FCLEAN`.

NAME: FCLEAN2
DESCRIPTION: Complement of fluid fraction cleanup coefficient for fluid #2. Throws away fluid #2 "mist" regions where local (isolated) fluid fraction complement, :math:`1-F`, within a cell is less than :envvar:`FCLEAN2`.

NAME: EPSADJ
DESCRIPTION: Multiplier for the calculated pressure iteration convergence criterion

NAME: ALPHAMB
DESCRIPTION: Controls weighting of Neumann- and Dirichlet-type boundary conditions for pressure at inter-block boundaries:

NAME: IAUTOSET
DESCRIPTION: Flag to use algorithm to automatically adjust subspace size used for GMRES pressure solver.

NAME: EPSELS
DESCRIPTION: Convergence adjustment for implicit elastic stress model

NAME: EPSVIS
DESCRIPTION: Convergence adjustment for implicit viscous model

NAME: RESFILE
DESCRIPTION: Name of the restart source file, e.g. :envvar:`resfile` = :file:`'flsgrf.dat'`

NAME: DELTR
DESCRIPTION: Initial time-step size for restart calculation

NAME: IRSAT
DESCRIPTION: Flag to control input parameters for non-condensable gas model

NAME: EPSADJCG
DESCRIPTION: Multiplier for the convergence criterion for the implicit core gas pressure solver.

NAME: TAURLXCG
DESCRIPTION: Time over which the metal pressure at core surface is averaged

NAME: ISSDIMCG
DESCRIPTION: Sub-scaling dimension of the binder array. Each computational cell within a core is subdivided into :envvar:`ISSDIMCG` equal sub-cells in each coordinate direction to store binder concentration.

NAME: IFTHEXP
DESCRIPTION: Thermal expansion flag for flow with density a function of temperature

NAME: STRNGMOB
DESCRIPTION: Global coefficient of Stronge's restitution during collision between coupled-motion GMO components and other components and walls. Values should be between 0.0 and 1.0.

NAME: FRCMOB
DESCRIPTION: Global coefficient of friction during collision between coupled-motion GMO components and other components and walls

NAME: BTMSHR
DESCRIPTION: Drag coefficient for quadratic bottom shear stress. Used when :envvar:`ISWATLOC` = 1 and :envvar:`IFVISWAT` = 2.

NAME: SSACC
DESCRIPTION: Damping rate coefficient for steady-state acceleration for free surface flows. Used when positive, and :envvar:`NMAT` = 1 and :envvar:`ITB` = 1.

NAME: CD_MAX
DESCRIPTION: Maximum value of drag coefficient of bottom shear stress

NAME: THCGAP
DESCRIPTION: Thermal conductivity of the gas in the gap, e.g., air.

NAME: EFE1GAP
DESCRIPTION: Emissivity of solidified fluid #1 in the gap

NAME: OFFSET
DESCRIPTION: Distance in z-direction above the bottom of a reservoir at which velocity is computed and stored as part of the Hydraulic data output.

NAME: IPDIS
DESCRIPTION: Flag for initial hydrostatic pressure distribution

NAME: IEVENT_RST
DESCRIPTION: Active simulation control events restart flag

NAME: PLTFRC
DESCRIPTION: Interval for restart spatial plots based on fill fraction (:envvar:`IEDT` = 2) or solid fraction (:envvar:`IEDT` = 3).

NAME: PLTAFRC
DESCRIPTION: Interval for selected spatial plots based on fill fraction (:envvar:`IEDT` = 2) or solid fraction (:envvar:`IEDT` = 3).

NAME: ESPRTDT
DESCRIPTION: Short print wall clock interval (in minutes).

NAME: PRTFRC
DESCRIPTION: Interval for long prints based on fill fraction (:envvar:`IEDT` = 2) or solid fraction (:envvar:`IEDT` = 3).

NAME: IEDT
DESCRIPTION: Selects the basis for long print and spatial plot intervals

NAME: CONHT
DESCRIPTION: Safety factor for explicit heat conduction/transfer time step size stability limit

NAME: CONFS
DESCRIPTION: Safety factor for free surface stability

NAME: CONSHR
DESCRIPTION: Multiplier for sub-time stepping in rapid shrinkage model and microporosity models when used together with the implicit heat transfer solver, :envvar:`IMPHTC` :math:`>` 0.

NAME: FRCTTSE
DESCRIPTION: Friction coefficient between Thermal Stress Evolution (TSE) region and neighboring Fluid Structure Interaction (FSI) components. A negative value indicates that the coefficient is infinite (i.e., tangential traction is not limited), and a positive value indicates the friction coefficient. Its value represents the ratio between the limit of the magnitude of tangential traction to the normal traction between the TSE region and the component face. Physical values are typically less than 1.0.

NAME: FSI_MEMORY
DESCRIPTION: Amount of additional memory (in GB) that may be used to store data structures that can significantly speed up the FSI solver.

NAME: IMPADV2
DESCRIPTION: Time step control flag for implicit advection option, :envvar:`IMPADV` = 1

NAME: V_THRESH
DESCRIPTION: Velocity threshold for implicit advection. Cells with velocity above :envvar:`V_THRESH` are treated implicitly. Used when :envvar:`IMPADV` = 1 and :envvar:`IMPADV2` = 1.

NAME: DT_THRESH
DESCRIPTION: Time step threshold for implicit advection. Cells with local advective stability limit below :envvar:`DT_THRESH` are treated implicitly. Used when :envvar:`IMPADV` = 1 and :envvar:`IMPADV2` = 2.

NAME: VOL_CORR_TIME
DESCRIPTION: Characteristic time for fluid #1 volume correction. Defaults to 10.0 when :envvar:`IVOL_CORR_TIME` = 1. Must be positive when :envvar:`IVOL_CORR_TIME` = 2.

NAME: EPSFSI
DESCRIPTION: Fluid-structure interaction (FSI) and thermal stress evolution (TSE) convergence criterion.

NAME: CGFOB
DESCRIPTION: Coefficient of gravity effect on metal/foam heat transfer for the lost foam casting model (used in conjunction with foam component roughness).

NAME: HFLV1
DESCRIPTION: Heat transfer coefficient for fluid #1 to type 1 void

NAME: HFLV2
DESCRIPTION: Heat transfer coefficient for fluid #1 to type 2 void

NAME: HFLV3
DESCRIPTION: Heat transfer coefficient for fluid #1 to type 3 void

NAME: HFLEM1
DESCRIPTION: Emissivity for fluid #1 to type 1 void

NAME: HFLEM2
DESCRIPTION: Emissivity for fluid #1 to type 2 void

NAME: HFLEM3
DESCRIPTION: Emissivity for fluid #1 to type 3 void

NAME: RHOAIR
DESCRIPTION: Air density for use in the calculation of wind shear stress on horizontal fluid surfaces, air drag for mooring lines,

NAME: ITHTMX
DESCRIPTION: Maximum number of temperature iterations per cycle

NAME: IDTHT
DESCRIPTION: Maximum number of temperature iterations before the time step is reduced

NAME: ITMAX
DESCRIPTION: Maximum number of pressure iterations per cycle

NAME: ITFLMX
DESCRIPTION: Maximum number of pressure iteration failures allowed

NAME: MRSTRT
DESCRIPTION: Restart number for GMRES pressure solver. It is not allowed to be less than 15 or greater than 100.

NAME: ITESMX
DESCRIPTION: Maximum number of implicit elastic stress iterations

NAME: IDTES
DESCRIPTION: Maximum number of elastic iterations before the time step is reduced

NAME: ITVSMX
DESCRIPTION: Maximum number of implicit viscous stress iterations

NAME: ITMAXCG
DESCRIPTION: Maximum number of core gas pressure solver iterations

NAME: ITSHMX
DESCRIPTION: Maximum number of volume iterations for the simple shrinkage model

NAME: MRSTRTFSI
DESCRIPTION: Restart number for GMRES Fluid structure interaction (FSI) and thermal stress evolution (TSE) solver. It is not allowed to be less than 6 or greater than 1000.

NAME: ITMAXFSI
DESCRIPTION: Maximum number of Fluid Structure Interaction (FSI) or Thermal Stress Evolution (TSE) solver iterations

NAME: IITMX
DESCRIPTION: Inner iteration count maximum for non-linear equation-of-state

NAME: NSTSHR
DESCRIPTION: Maximum number of sub-time steps for simple shrinkage and microporosity models

NAME: EPS
DESCRIPTION: Cutoff value for the evaluation of area and volume fractions

NAME: VFCLEAN
DESCRIPTION: Volume fraction cleanup coefficient. Fully blocks cells where local (isolated) open volume fraction is less than :envvar:`VFCLEAN`.

NAME: NCFLMX
DESCRIPTION: Maximum number of consecutive convection or pressure convergence failures allowed

NAME: UNITS
DESCRIPTION: Character string used to identify units (up to 10 characters)

NAME: TUNITS
DESCRIPTION: Character string used to identify temperature units (up to 10 characters)

NAME: MUNITS
DESCRIPTION: Character string used to identify mass units when "Custom" option is chosen (up to 10 characters)

NAME: LUNITS
DESCRIPTION: Character string used to identify length units when "Custom" option is chosen (up to 10 characters)

NAME: TIMUNITS
DESCRIPTION: Character string used to identify time units when "Custom" option is chosen (up to 10 characters)

NAME: CUNITS
DESCRIPTION: Character string used to identify charge units when "Custom" option is chosen (up to 10 characters)

NAME: RFNC
DESCRIPTION: Specific gas constant for the non-condensable gas component.

NAME: CVNC
DESCRIPTION: Specific heat for the non-condensable gas component.

NAME: GAMMA
DESCRIPTION: Exponent in void region equation of state, ``P*V^GAMMA = constant``. Zero or negative value indicates constant pressure. :envvar:`GAMMA` = ratio of specific heats of 'void' gas C\ :sub:`p`/C\ :sub:`v`, assumed constant.

NAME: DFCD
DESCRIPTION: Drag coefficient for a particle of the dispersed phase moving in the continuous phase.

NAME: DFDIAM
DESCRIPTION: Average particle diameter of the dispersed phase. Used when :envvar:`IDSIZE=` = 0.

NAME: DFDIAM_INI
DESCRIPTION: Initial particle diameter of the dispersed phase. Used when :envvar:`IDSIZE=` = 1.

NAME: RZMLT
DESCRIPTION: Constant multiplier for dynamically-computed Richardson-Zaki coefficient

NAME: PERMDER
DESCRIPTION: Fluid electric permittivity derivative with respect to temperature

NAME: CONDDER
DESCRIPTION: Fluid electric conductivity derivative with respect to temperature

NAME: FREQUEN
DESCRIPTION: Angular frequency of external electric field

NAME: CANGLE
DESCRIPTION: Static contact angle (in degrees) for fluid #1 wall adhesion

NAME: FRCOF
DESCRIPTION: Coefficient of friction between fluid and solid walls for the partial slip model. A zero value corresponds to free slip and an infinite value to no-slip. A negative value turns off the partial slip model. Also see :envvar:`OFRCOF` in namelist :envvar:`OBS`.

NAME: GASDEN
DESCRIPTION: Density of the fluid surrounding granular material (gas for :envvar:`IFGRN` = 1, liquid for :envvar:`IFGRN` = 2)

NAME: GASVIS
DESCRIPTION: Dynamic viscosity of the fluid surrounding granular material (gas for :envvar:`IFGRN` = 1, liquid for :envvar:`IFGRN` = 2)

NAME: CVELGRN
DESCRIPTION: The absolute value of :envvar:`CVELGRN` is used as multiplier for threshold packing velocity. A larger value results in earlier packing. When :envvar:`CVELGRN` is negative, then full jamming is not produced - the granular mixture continues to move even at packing density.

NAME: PGASMP
DESCRIPTION: Critical pressure below which pores can form during solidification. Used in the micro-porosity model, :envvar:`IMUPOR` = 1.

NAME: RHOCARBIDE
DESCRIPTION: Density of the carbide formed during eutectic reaction

NAME: RHOGRAPHITE
DESCRIPTION: Density of the graphite formed during the eutectic reaction

NAME: RHOENDIRON
DESCRIPTION: Density of the solid phase formed after eutectic reaction

NAME: FSEUTE
DESCRIPTION: Solid fraction at the end of eutectic reaction

NAME: FLUID1
DESCRIPTION: Character string allowing user to identify fluid #1 (up to 50 characters)
SET_VALUE: 'Aluminum Silicon Alloy A356 Auburn Univ data'

NAME: MUC00
DESCRIPTION: Coefficient in strain rate-dependent viscosity model

NAME: MUC0
DESCRIPTION: Coefficient in strain rate-dependent viscosity model

NAME: MUC1
DESCRIPTION: Coefficient in strain rate-dependent viscosity model

NAME: MUC4
DESCRIPTION: Coefficient in strain rate-dependent viscosity model

NAME: MUC2
DESCRIPTION: Coefficient in strain rate-dependent viscosity model

NAME: MUC3
DESCRIPTION: Coefficient in strain rate-dependent viscosity model

NAME: MUTHN0
DESCRIPTION: First coefficient in the strain rate-dependent rate of viscosity decrease (flow thinning) in the thixotropic model

NAME: MUTHN1
DESCRIPTION: Second coefficient in the strain rate-dependent rate of viscosity decrease (flow thinning) in the thixotropic model

NAME: MUTHK
DESCRIPTION: Rate of viscosity increase (flow thickening) in the thixotropic model

NAME: MUI
DESCRIPTION: Initial coefficient of dynamic viscosity for thixotropic flow model

NAME: THEXF1
DESCRIPTION: Volumetric thermal expansion coefficient for fluid #1

NAME: THEXF2
DESCRIPTION: Volumetric thermal expansion coefficient for fluid #2

NAME: RF2
DESCRIPTION: Specific gas constant of fluid #2 (:envvar:`RF2` = (:envvar:`GAMMA`-1)•:envvar:`CV2` for a gamma-law gas)

NAME: POFL1
DESCRIPTION: Uniform power source per unit mass for fluid #1

NAME: POFL2
DESCRIPTION: Uniform power source per unit mass for fluid #2

NAME: TSTAR
DESCRIPTION: Reference temperature for temperature-dependent fluid properties

NAME: CLHT1
DESCRIPTION: Latent heat of fusion in fluid #1

NAME: THEXS1
DESCRIPTION: Volumetric thermal expansion coefficient of solidified phase of fluid #1 (used in elastic stress model).

NAME: ADJSHR
DESCRIPTION: Multiplication coefficient for volume change during solidification. Values must not be negative.

NAME: FSCR
DESCRIPTION: Critical solid fraction above which metal has no fluidity

NAME: FSCO
DESCRIPTION: Fraction of solid at coherency point.

NAME: CSTAR
DESCRIPTION: Reference solute concentration for concentration-dependent density. :envvar:`CSTAR` also corresponds to :envvar:`TS1` and :envvar:`TL1` on the phase diagram.

NAME: PV1
DESCRIPTION: Absolute pressure value on the saturation curve that corresponds to temperature :envvar:`TV1`. The saturation curve defines a relationship between saturation pressure and temperature.

NAME: TV1
DESCRIPTION: Temperature value on the saturation curve that corresponds to pressure :envvar:`PV1`. The saturation curve defines a relationship between saturation pressure and temperature.

NAME: CLHV1
DESCRIPTION: Latent heat of vaporization/condensation constant (\ :envvar:`ICLHV1` = 0) *or* value at temperature :envvar:`THV1` (when :envvar:`ICLHV1` = 2)

NAME: RSIZE
DESCRIPTION: Dimensionless accommodation coefficient for the liquid/vapor evaporative phase change rate.

NAME: CVVAP
DESCRIPTION: Vapor specific heat at constant volume of vaporized fluid 1 (\ :envvar:`IPHCHG` = 4) or fluid 2 (\ :envvar:`IPHCHG` = 5).

NAME: TVEXP
DESCRIPTION: Exponent in the relationship between saturation pressure and temperature. For perfect gas :envvar:`TVEXP` is equal to (\ :envvar:`GAMMA` -1.0)*\ :envvar:`CVVAP`/\ :envvar:`CLHV1`. The saturation curve is defined by the Clapeyron equation:

NAME: TV0
DESCRIPTION: Superheat temperature. Liquid in the bulk is allowed to heat to :envvar:`TV0` degrees before it starts evaporating (or boiling).

NAME: PV0
DESCRIPTION: Partial pressure of vapor in void regions.

NAME: TC0
DESCRIPTION: Supercooling temperature. Gas in the bulk is allowed to cool to :envvar:`TC0` degrees before it starts condensing.

NAME: RHOF
DESCRIPTION: Density of fluid #1. For temperature-dependent density, fluid #1 density at T=\ :envvar:`TSTAR`.

NAME: SIGMA
DESCRIPTION: Surface tension coefficient; same as used in :ref:`SurfaceTensionProperties`.

NAME: SIGMA_DF
DESCRIPTION: Surface tension coefficient at the interface between two phases

NAME: EMODT1
DESCRIPTION: Fluid #1 shear elastic modulus temperature sensitivity

NAME: EMODT2
DESCRIPTION: Fluid #2 shear elastic modulus temperature sensitivity

NAME: MUS
DESCRIPTION: Additional viscosity coefficient for density- or solid-fraction-dependent viscosity model. Only used when :envvar:`MUS` :math:`>` 0.0.

NAME: ITHC1
DESCRIPTION: Flag for the definition of thermal conductivity of fluid #1

NAME: MOBLTY1
DESCRIPTION: Mobility factor for fluid #1. Positive values only. Is needed to define a Giesekus fluid.

NAME: MOBLTY2
DESCRIPTION: Mobility factor for fluid #2. Positive values only. Is needed to define a Giesekus fluid.

NAME: RELAX2
DESCRIPTION: Relaxation time of fluid #2 for Oldroyd-B viscoelasticity model. Any value less than or equal to 0.0 means that the relaxation time is infinite, that is, no relaxation.

NAME: RHOCAV
DESCRIPTION: Cavitation gas density, used with the empirical cavitation model, :envvar:`ICAV` = 1 and :envvar:`ICAVMODEL` = 1.

NAME: CAVPROD
DESCRIPTION: Empirical cavitation production coefficient, used with the empirical cavitation model, :envvar:`ICAV` = 1 and :envvar:`ICAVMODEL` = 1.

NAME: CAVDISS
DESCRIPTION: Empirical cavitation dissipation coefficient, used with the empirical cavitation model, :envvar:`ICAV` = 1 and :envvar:`ICAVMODEL` = 1.

NAME: IPGAUGE
DESCRIPTION: Pressure type, absolute or gauge, for all pressure quantities used in the simulation.

NAME: P_REFERENCE
DESCRIPTION: Absolute reference pressure. Defaults to 1 atm. in SI, CGS, engineering or custom units appropriately, based on :envvar:`UNITS` specified.

NAME: FSTSE
DESCRIPTION: Solid fraction for Thermal Stress Evolution (TSE) elements activation. 0 :math:`<` FSTSE :math:`<=` 1.

NAME: BLKMOD_LIQ
DESCRIPTION: Bulk modulus of liquid phase. Used in the micro-porosity model, :envvar:`IMUPOR` = 1.

NAME: BLKMOD_FSCR
DESCRIPTION: Bulk modulus of solidifing fluid at critical solid fraction :envvar:`FSCR`. Used in the micro-porosity model, :envvar:`IMUPOR` = 1.

NAME: MUVOID
DESCRIPTION: Dynamic viscosity of the void region. Used in the permeable mold model, :envvar:`IOBSVENT(n)` = 1.

NAME: DFESP_COEFF
DESCRIPTION: Escape rate coefficient for gas escape velocity at free surface

NAME: IDFAIR
DESCRIPTION: Flag to activate air entrainment model. A non-zero value activates the model.

NAME: SCRFCR
DESCRIPTION: Critical solid fraction. Represents the total solid fraction beyond which the sediment is completely packed.

NAME: CROUGH
DESCRIPTION: Roughness coefficient for surface of packed sediment bed (roughness :math:`k_s=c_{\rm{rough}} d_{50,\rm{packed}}`)

NAME: IDFCT
DESCRIPTION: Free surface defect tracking model flag

NAME: DFTSRF
DESCRIPTION: Coefficient of proportionality for free-surface-generated defects (defects created per unit time per unit area).

NAME: DFTFOB
DESCRIPTION: Coefficient of proportionality for foam residue (amount of foam residue per unit volume of decomposed solid foam).

NAME: DISSMTC
DESCRIPTION: Mass transfer coefficient for solid solute components

NAME: WEBCRIT
DESCRIPTION: Critical Weber number above which particles break up

NAME: CAPCRIT
DESCRIPTION: Critical capillary number above which particles break up

NAME: MAXECHRG
DESCRIPTION: Maximum iterations for coupled electric field-electric charge solver

NAME: MAXPHIT
DESCRIPTION: Maximum iterations for electric (external) potential solver

NAME: CONCEN
DESCRIPTION: Average ion concentration in bulk flow.

NAME: RMSCS_SLDG
DESCRIPTION: Turbulent diffusion coefficient multiplier for sludge

NAME: CMDFT
DESCRIPTION: Molecular diffusion coefficient of free surface defects

NAME: CMDFT_LF
DESCRIPTION: Molecular diffusion coefficient of foam residue defects

NAME: RMDFT
DESCRIPTION: Turbulent diffusion coefficient multiplier for free surface defects

NAME: RMDFT_LF
DESCRIPTION: Turbulent diffusion coefficient multiplier for foam residue defects

NAME: CMSEG
DESCRIPTION: Molecular diffusion coefficient of the solute mass concentration

NAME: RMSEG
DESCRIPTION: Turbulent diffusion coefficient multiplier for the solute mass concentration

NAME: CMSCR
DESCRIPTION: Molecular diffusion coefficient of the suspended sediment

NAME: RMSCR
DESCRIPTION: Turbulent diffusion coefficient multiplier for the suspended sediment

NAME: IFILL1
DESCRIPTION: Flag to activate the recording of the first and last time a cell fills with fluid #1

NAME: IRESDT
DESCRIPTION: Flag used to compute fluid residence time (the amount of time fluid is present in the flow domain)

NAME: ICONTACT
DESCRIPTION: Flag used to activate fluid/wall contact time output

NAME: IPATH
DESCRIPTION: Flag used to compute distance traveled by fluid from its initial location or from the inlet (mesh boundary or mass source)

NAME: TV2M
DESCRIPTION: Reference temperature for ideal gas equation of state.

NAME: SIZE
DESCRIPTION: Cell size to be approximated for a uniform mesh. Used when :envvar:`IF_SIZE` = 1. :envvar:`SIZE` is used for directions for which a domain has been specified by :envvar:`PX`, :envvar:`PY`, and/or :envvar:`PZ`, but not the number of cells (:envvar:`NXCELT`, :envvar:`NYCELT`, or :envvar:`NZCELT`).

NAME: SIZE
DESCRIPTION: Cell size to be approximated for a uniform mesh. Used when :envvar:`IF_SIZE` = 1. :envvar:`SIZE` is used for directions for which a domain has been specified by :envvar:`PX`, :envvar:`PY`, and/or :envvar:`PZ`, but not the number of cells (:envvar:`NXCELT`, :envvar:`NYCELT`, or :envvar:`NZCELT`).

NAME: OVERLAP
DESCRIPTION: The extent of the overlap (in terms of length) of a conforming block into

NAME: AVRCK
DESCRIPTION: Cell volume fractions are adjusted in so-called *sliver* cells so that the area/volume fraction ratios do not exceed this value.

NAME: TOLERANCE_GAP
DESCRIPTION: Gap size tolerance. Gaps that are smaller than the tolerance will be closed.

NAME: TOLERANCE_SKIN
DESCRIPTION: Skin size tolerance. Skins that are smaller than the tolerance will be converted to the base component which they

NAME: SPRAY
DESCRIPTION: Spray cooling properties for thermal die cycling
